                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.5151/263: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dominian</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 14, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Please send by airmail the report requested in Department’s instruction No.
                    309, of January 21, also reporting whether the oil companies have a possibility
                    of obtaining through legal action redress for the alleged discriminations in
                    favor of the State-owned company. What are the prospects of American oil
                    companies arriving at an early satisfactory adjustment of their various
                    difficulties with the Government?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
